snippet.textDisplay: Asalamualaikum dear brothers and sisters, someone has brought to my attention that ‘Tajdar-e-haram’ is shirk as it is calling out to someone rather than Allah Subhanahu Wa Ta’Ala for help. We love Prophet Muhammad (Salallahu Alaihi Wa Salam) so much, but we do not worship him (Salallahu Alaihi Wa Sallam) or call out to him for help thus, it is important for us to avoid such phrases or listening to naats. Even though the intention was good and I love brother Atif Aslam, again it is essential to avoid this and recognize it as shirk and share this knowledge with others!
snippet.textOriginal: Asalamualaikum dear brothers and sisters, someone has brought to my attention that ‘Tajdar-e-haram’ is shirk as it is calling out to someone rather than Allah Subhanahu Wa Ta’Ala for help.
